      • wrap

        static <A> Set<A> wrap(java.util.Set<A> underlying)
        Wraps a Set in a Set.

        Does *not* make a copy of the given Set. The Vector will hold a reference to the given Set, but will not alter it in any way.

        Since bearers of this Set will be unable to mutate or gain access to the underlying data, it is safe to share.

        Since this does not make a copy of the underlying data, be aware that anyone that holds a direct reference to it the java.util.Set can still mutate it.
